  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who has shown remorse by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While the breach of trust is significant, a 10-year sentence suggested by the spectator is disproportionate to both the amount embezzled and legal sentencing guidelines for white-collar crimes of this magnitude. Taking into account the need for restitution and the absence of a criminal record, a sentence of 6 months serves as a punitive measure that acknowledges the crime without being excessively punitive.",
  "verdict": 6
}
